This research harness was instantiated from the
[research-harness template](https://github.com/modeled-information-format/research-harness-template)
with Copier, so it can pull later template improvements with `bash scripts/update.sh`
(which verifies release provenance before applying).

- **Owner:** {{ author_name }}
- **Seed topic:** `okf-mif-knowledge-spine` — an archived example research corpus
  (OKF + MIF knowledge spine) shipped with the template as a worked showcase. Run
  `/start` to research your own topics.

## Updating

When the upstream template gains skills, gates, or schema versions, re-apply them:

```bash
bash scripts/update.sh
```

`scripts/update.sh` is the only supported update path: it verifies the target release's
provenance (fail-closed), then runs `copier update` — a three-way merge that reconciles
your local edits — only on success. The capability a living template needs (SPEC §7).
